<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910513-0060</DOCNO><DOCID>910513-0060.</DOCID><HL>   Financing Business:   General Host Corp.</HL><DATE>05/13/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C8</SO><CO>   GH</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>OTHER SPECIALTY RETAILERS OF LIMITED PRODUCT LINES (OTS)STOCK AND BOND REGISTRATIONS, PRICINGS (REG)ALL SPECIALTY RETAILERS (RTS)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)</IN><NS>BOND AND STOCK REGISTRATIONS AND PRICINGS (REG)STOCK andamp; OTHER MARKET NEWS (STK)</NS><RE>CONNECTICUT (CT)</RE><LP>   GENERAL HOST Corp., Stamford, Conn., said it plans to makea public offering for its Calloway's Nursery Inc. unit. Theoperator of lawn and garden product stores, in a Securitiesand Exchange Commission filing, said the proposed offering isfor all 4.2 million shares of Calloway's Nursery. GeneralHost owns 3.2 million shares, or 80%, of Calloway's, an11-store garden center chain in the Dallas/Fort Worth area.In the fiscal year ended Jan. 28, Calloway's was profitableon sales of $22.1 million, a General Host spokesman said.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>